metadata.title: Cessna 182 Skylane
aws::graph::propositions: Argentine Federal Police operates one Cessna A182L since 2001.
The Cessna A182L operated by Argentine Federal Police is still in service for training as of 2020.
Belgium Federal Police operates Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft.
Transport Canada operated one Cessna 182 Skylane.
Transport Canada sold its Cessna 182 Skylane in 2010.
Civil Air Patrol in the United States operates Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft.
Civil Air Patrol uses Cessna 182 Skylane for inland search and rescue.
Civil Air Patrol uses Cessna 182 Skylane for coastal search and rescue.
Civil Air Patrol uses Cessna 182 Skylane for homeland security support.
Civil Air Patrol uses Cessna 182 Skylane for airborne communications repeater service.
Federal Bureau of Investigation operates at least 27 Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft.
Federal Bureau of Investigation uses Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft as surveillance aircraft.
The surveillance Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft operated by Federal Bureau of Investigation are equipped with optical equipment.
The surveillance Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft operated by Federal Bureau of Investigation are equipped with infrared equipment.
The surveillance Cessna 182 Skylane aircraft operated by Federal Bureau of Investigation are equipped with cellphone ELINT equipment.

text:
### Government operators
 Argentina
Argentine Federal Police - one A182L from 2001 is still in service for training as of 2020.
 Belgium
Federal Police
 Canada
Transport Canada  one, sold in 2010
 United States
Civil Air Patrol  used for inland and coastal search and rescue, homeland security support, and airborne communications repeater service
Federal Bureau of Investigation - at least 27 used as surveillance aircraft equipped with optical, infrared and cellphone ELINT equipment
